headlines.description: Chimezie Metu had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and No. 10 Southern California routed Cal State Fullerton 84-42 on Friday night to open the season with its highest ranking since 1974-75.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 10 USC rolls past Cal State Fullerton 84-42 in opener

headlines.description: Jordan Murphy scored a career-high 35 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, Reggie Lynch added 15 points and 10 rebounds and 15th-ranked Minnesota overpowered South Carolina Upstate in the season opener for a 92-77 victory on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Murphy, No. 15 Minnesota overpower SC Upstate 92-77

headlines.description: Nick Garth had 23 points and eight rebounds, Colton Weisbrod added 15 points and 13 boards for his 11th career double-double, and Lamar beat Tulsa 74-67 on Friday night in an opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar beats Tulsa 74-67 on the road in season opener

headlines.description: Tony Carr scored 24 of his career-high 33 points in the second half and Penn State beat Campbell 86-75 on Friday in the first game for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carr leads Penn State with career night against Campbell

headlines.description: Maliek White scored 13 points and Kyron Cartwright had 10 points and distributed 10 assists to lead Providence to its season-opening win beating Houston Baptist 84-55 on Friday night in a 2K Classic tournament opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: White leads attack, Providence dumps Houston Baptist 84-55

headlines.description: Devin Sibley scored 23 points, Daniel Fowler added 15 more and Furman cruised to a 101-48 win over Bob Jones in the season opener for both teams Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Furman coasts to 101-48 win over Bob Jones

headlines.description: Kendrick Nunn had a career-high 36 points and six assists, Martez Walker added 17 points, and Oakland beat Fort Wayne 85-71 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nunn scores 36, Oakland beats Fort Wayne 85-71

headlines.description: Josh Cunningham caught a lob from Xeyrius Williams and laid it in with one second left, and Dayton opened the Anthony Grant era with a 78-77 win over Ball State in Friday night's season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dayton opens Grant era with 78-77 win over Ball State

headlines.description: David Nichols scored 18 points and Greig Stire added 15 points and 12 rebounds- seven on the offensive end -- and Albany held off Iona 69-67 on Friday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nichols ices game at FT line helping Albany over Iona 69-67

headlines.description: D'Marcus Simonds had a triple-double to lead Georgia State in a 90-50 thumping of Carver Bible College on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simonds has triple-double, Georgia St. beats Carver 90-50

headlines.description: Lovell Cabbil scored 14 points and Isaiah Williams and Ezra Talbert each scored 13 and Liberty controlled Division-III level Summit from the outset in an 87-42 win on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cabbil does damage early in Liberty's 87-42 win over Summit

headlines.description: Stanford Robinson had 18 points and Andre Berry added 15 as Rhode Island opened the season with an 84-60 win over UNC Asheville on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson, Berry lead Rhode Island to an 84-60 win in opener

headlines.description: Daryl Macon and Jaylen Barford scored 16 points each to lead six players in double figures as Arkansas rolled to a season-opening 95-56 win over Samford on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Macon, Barford pace Arkansas to opening win over Samford

headlines.description: Bryce Brown scored a career-high 31 points and Auburn opened the season with a 102-74 victory over Norfolk State Friday night in a matchup of teams missing two of their top players.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown leads Auburn to 102-74 opening win over Norfolk State

headlines.description: Shake Milton tossed in 28 points and SMU overcame a seven-point halftime deficit to beat Maryland-Baltimore County, 78-67 in the season opener Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Milton scores 28, leads SMU comeback to beat UMBC, 78-67

headlines.description: Jon Elmore scored a career-high 38 points to lead Marshall in a 102-91 overtime victory over Tennessee-Martin on Friday night in a season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Elmore scores 38; Marshall beats UT-Martin 102-91 in OT

headlines.description: Chris Cokley scored a career-high 26 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as Alabama-Birmingham rolled past Jacksonville, 96-67 in the season opener Friday Night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cokley's 26 pts, 13 boards lead UAB past Jacksonville, 96-67

headlines.description: Ryan Richardson scored 20 points, Zach Braxton added 18 and Weber State held off Utah State 65-59 on Friday night in the season opener for both teams.

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
